The `Separator` component is a reusable UI element used to visually separate content. It is built using `@radix-ui/react-separator` and provides a customizable way to add horizontal or vertical dividers.

## Exports

- `Separator`: The main React component for rendering a separator.

## Props

The `Separator` component accepts the following props:

- `className`: Optional. Additional CSS classes to apply to the separator.
- `orientation`: Optional. Determines the orientation of the separator. Can be `'horizontal'` (default) or `'vertical'`.
- `decorative`: Optional. A boolean value indicating whether the separator is purely decorative. Defaults to `true`.
- `...props`: All other props are passed down to the underlying `SeparatorPrimitive.Root` component.

## Usage Example

```tsx
import { Separator } from '@/components/ui/separator';

function MyComponent() {
  return (
    <div>
      <p>Content above the separator.</p>
      <Separator /> {/* Horizontal separator */}
      <p>Content below the separator.</p>

      <div className="flex items-center h-32">
        <span>Content to the left</span>
        <Separator orientation="vertical" /> {/* Vertical separator */}
        <span>Content to the right</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}

export default MyComponent;
```
